        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Hendersonville, or 4 miles north of Saluda, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saluda, Chimney Rock State Park, Dana, Edneyville, and East Flat
Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
